# Page Summarization
# Demonstrates Copilot summarizing the content of a specific SharePoint page.

[var: SITE = https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]
[category: Site & Copilot]

[section: setup]

Verify the Welcome page loads and Copilot is accessible before the demo.

[navigate: ${SITE}]

[open-chat]

Chat pane is open. Starting a fresh session now.

[new-chat]

[section: demo]

[navigate: ${SITE}]

We're starting on the home page. Copilot can summarize any page you're on —
not just the whole site. Let's open the chat and ask for a summary.

[pause]

[open-chat]

[prompt: Summarize this page]

[wait]

Copilot has summarized the Welcome page. The summary is grounded in what's
actually on this page — text, sections, any embedded content.

Compare this to a manual "executive summary" — same output, zero effort.

[pause]

Now let's ask it to pull out just the key takeaways. This is the kind of
follow-up that makes Copilot useful for someone who just landed on an
unfamiliar page.

[prompt: What are the three most important things a new visitor should know from this page?]

[wait]

Copilot extracted a concise list. This is useful for onboarding flows,
handoffs, and knowledge transfer — any situation where someone needs to
quickly understand a page they haven't seen before.

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/page-summarization.png]

[section: reset]

This demo is read-only. Navigate back to the home page to reset the view.

[navigate: ${SITE}]
